{{fanpov|date=December 2016}} [[File:Dr. Asim Hussain.jpg|thumb|Asim Hussain addressing public gathering]] '''Asim Hussain, SI, HI''' <ref>{{cite web|last1=|first1=|title=Dr. Asim Hussain|url=http://www.pakistanherald.com/profile/dr-asim-hussain-599|website=Pakistan Herald }}</ref> is active in the fields of health, education, and Pakistani politics. He is chairman of [[Dr. Ziauddin Group of Hospitals|Ziauddin Group of Hospitals]] in Karachi, and former Advisor of [[Government of Pakistan|Prime Minister for Ministry of Oil and Natural Resources, Pakistan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2014/07/19/city/karachi/zardari-takes-notice-of-health-ministry-dispute/|title=Zardari takes notice of health ministry dispute|website=www.pakistantoday.com.pk}}</ref> He serves as the Chairman of Higher Commission of Sindh and Chairman of [[Petroleum Institute of Pakistan]].
In recognition of his services to the nation in the fields of education and health care he has been conferred with the [[Sitara-i-Imtiaz]] and [[Hilal-i-Imtiaz]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hussain|first1=Dr. Asim|title=Nishan i imtiaz|url=http://www.thenews.com.pk/Todays-News-2-167144-President-grants-different-awards-to-citizens-foreigners|website=www.thenews.com.pk|publisher=The News|accessdate=24 March 2013}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|last1=Hussain|first1=Dr. Asim|title=Hilal i Imtiaz|url=http://www.brecorder.com/general-news/epaper:/1167016:president-decorates-civil-military-personnel-for-awards-on-pakistan-day/?date=2013-03-24|website=Brecorder.com.pk|publisher=Business Recorder|accessdate=24 March 2013}}</ref>
On the 27th of August 2015 Asim Hussain was detained by the Authorities in an ongoing operation within the city of Karachi launched by the [[Pakistani Army]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1202960|title=Dr Asim Hussain reportedly detained by security personnel in Karachi|first=Imtiaz|last=Ali|date=26 August 2015|publisher=}}</ref>
== Early life == Hussain was born in Karachi, Pakistan on 28 November 1953, to Ejaz Fatima and Tajammul Hussain, the founding members of the [[Dr. Ziauddin Group of Hospitals]].{{Citation needed|date= June 2018}}
== Educational Background == Hussain received his early education from the [[Karachi Grammar School]] and later enrolled in the [[Cadet College, Petaro]].{{Citation needed|date= June 2018}} After serving a brief period in the [[Pakistan Army]], Hussain retired as a Lieutenant and chose to pursue the degree of [[MBBS]].{{Citation needed|date= June 2018}} He graduated from [[Dow Medical College]] (now, Dow University of Health Sciences) Karachi in 1978 and went to Europe for further studies.{{Citation needed|date= June 2018}} He is a member of [[College of Physicians and Surgeons Pakistan]] (CPS). in 1981 and continued his studies in [[Vienna]], [[Austria]]. After returning to Pakistan, he entered politics.{{Citation needed|date= June 2018}}
== Early Professional Career == He is the Chairman of the Dr. Ziauddin Group of Hospitals. In 1995, Hussain established the [[Ziauddin University]], a chartered institution of the Provincial Assembly of Sindh and accredited by the [[Higher Education Commission]] (HEC) of Pakistan.{{Citation needed|date= June 2018}}
Other positions:<ref>{{cite web|first1=Kazi Zulkader |last1=Siddiqui|url=http://www.petaro.org/cadets%201957-69/695-AsimHussain.htm|website=Petaro|title=Asim Hussain, 695/Ayub }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=|first1=|url=http://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/tag/dr-asim-hussain/|website= |publisher=Pakistan Today|title=TAG ARCHIVES: DR ASIM HUSSAIN}}</ref> * Honorary Personal Physician to the President of Pakistan, since December 12, 2009 * Advisor/Federal Minister Petroleum & Natural Resource from May, 2011 until May, 2013 * Advisor to the Prime Minister for Petroleum & Natural Resources/Federal Minister from November, 2008 until August, 2009 * Chairman, National Reconstruction Bureau with the status of Federal Minister from May, 2008 until November, 2009
